The ashes of the ladies, whose disreputable actions are here recorded, have long been covered by the Latian and Flaminian ways; nor have their follies, or their vices, much similarity with those of modern times.

It would seem from internal evidence, that 11115 Satire was written under Domitian. It has few political allusions, and from its subject might not have been displeasing to that ferocious hypocrite, who affected at various times awonderful anxiety to restrain the licentionsness of the age! GIF.
